						<summary>

						<p>This is an inscription of one line in early Brāhmī characters (of the Aśokan period) engraved on the overhanging rock of a cave on the floor of which are cut seven stone beds, popularly known as <hi rend="italic">Pāṇḍavar-paḍukkai.</hi> This along with similar inscriptions from other places in the South have been published by Shri K.V. Subrahmanya Aiyar in a paper read before the Oriental Conference held at Madras in 1924.</p>						

						</summary>
